The European Equality Summit, which this year is hosted by France, the current presidency of the European Union, has begun today in Paris.
Lívia Járóková, a member of the European People’s Party for the Fidesz movement, as one of the main speakers of the expert discussion in her message addressed to the plenary session, drew attention to segregation in education, as it is one of the most serious injuries affecting Roma children, and also the most serious obstacle to their implementation.
