“We need to break the vicious circle of poverty, segregation and unemployment, we need to give Roma children the opportunities given by the democratic space so that they can participate in the future of Europe as full-fledged citizens,” she said.
Everyone is guaranteed the goal of the European Summit on Equality, held annually since last year’s meeting in Berlin, to provide a separate forum to contribute to the achievement of the objectives of equality and elimination of discrimination set out at European and national level.
