It is possible to greatly limit these damage by looking for solutions such as reducing the level and duration of exposure.
In its view, the Scientific Committee of the EU states that users of portable music instruments, if they use loud music (more than 89 decibels) for only five hours a week, will exceed the current limits corresponding to the maximum permitted noise at the workplace.
